		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">We propose to assess the properties of a new class of thin film transistor which we believe will make a major impact in electronic systems and circuits. The transistor named the source gated transistor has a number of advantages compared with its nearest relative, the field effect transistor. Transistors will be fabricated in hydrogenated amorphous silicon and assessed in the context of active matrix addressing of current driven emissive displays. We propose to examine both analogue and digital behaviour and the potential of the source gated transistor at high frequencies. The main objective is to obtain a good understanding of the behaviour of the source gated transistor and its benefits not only for active matrix addressing but for electronics as a whole.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
